					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">As for pulse generators, dedicate at least a byte for PWM per channel. Besides finer granularity (making sweeps and a bunch of timbres possible), you can get octave-like overtones this way. Example waveform: --__-_-_<br /><br />Another cheap application is to use flip-flops to get frequency division, and thus get suboctaves. you'd need active control of the sum/mixer to make it versatile.</div>

					
